sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1675009
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: a device to produce alkali and neutralize the external acidic environment
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Uses an acid induced promoter asr(BBa_K1170000), strong RBS(BBa_B0034),alkaline substance producing gene gadA coding region(BBa_K1675003).Will produce alkali under acidic environment and neutralize the external pH.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Hui Luo

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1170000
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: An acid inducible promoter of the acid shock response (asr) gene, extracted from E. coli K12. This part can be used to generate pH based response in any biological system.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Rohit Satija
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This part was extracted from the genome of E. coli K12
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The sequence provided in literature indicated a consensus sequence for the Pho Box just before the transcription start site

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1675003
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The gene GadA (glutamate decarboxylase A) can be cloned from Escherichia coli str. K-12 substr. GadA is a functional gene for producing alkali. It catalyzes the proton-consuming conversion of glutamate to γ-amino butyric acid (GABA) whereas it converts glutamate to GABA by removing the α-carboxylate group of glutamate.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: JIAQI XU
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Escherichia coli str. K-12 substr. Sequence found through Genbank http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nuccore/NC_000913.3?report=genbank&from=3666180&to=3667580&strand=true
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Mutation of TTT to TTC Phe.(site:129bp)
